tions empower learners, allowing them to draw from one another’s expertise to formulate and fulfill their own educational goals. In an increasingly networked world, developing such skills will, they argue, better prepare students to become self-directed, lifelong learners.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 0aDistance EducationvTextbooks. 0aEducationvTextbooks. 0aGeneral educationvTextbooks. 0aTheory and practice of education. 7aEDUCATION / Distance, Open & Online Education.2bisacsh  ablended learning.  aeducational technology.  alearning communities.  alearning management systems.  alifelong learners.  anetworked learning.  aself-directed learning.  asocial media.1 aAnderson, Terry, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package 2014z978311127407208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2014z978311127709740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781927356814423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781927356814/original  a978-3-11-127407-2  ACUP Complete eBook-Package 2014b2014  a978-3-11-127709-7  ACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2014b2014  aGBV-deGruyter-alles